msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Project-Id-Version: Orbiter Flights\n"
"Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8\n"
"Plural-Forms: nplurals=2; plural=(n != 1);\n"
"Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\n"

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:5
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fly me to the Moon! This flight recreates a complete lunar transfer with the Delta-glider from takeoff at the Kennedy Space Center to touchdown at Landing pad 1 of Brighton Beach Spaceport on the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:7
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The entire flight is replayed for you and doesn't require manual control, but the various manouvers will be explained along the way, together with the operation of the essential flight instruments."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:9
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Total flight time will be 3 days, 9 hours and 42 minutes. If you haven't got that much time, you can accelerate the simulation speed during the cruising phases of the flight."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:11
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Or simply make sure that the \"Play at recording speed\" option is enabled in the recorder dialog (Ctrl-F5). At recording speed, this tutorial will take about one hour."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:14
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The MFD instruments will play an important role during all phases of the flight. The camera is therefore set to \"glass cockpit\" view with the two onscreen MFDs projected onto the head-up display. If you prefer the panel or virtual cockpit views, you can select them by pressing F8."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:15
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The glider is fully fuelled and ready for takeoff at KSC SLF Runway 33, waiting for its launch window."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:17
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We want to launch into the orbital plane of the Moon to minimise the need for expensive plane changes later on."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:18
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Look at the map on the right MFD display. The green cross over Florida labelled 'GL-01' represents your current position. The green curve represents the projection of your orbital plane onto the surface, the red curve that of the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:19
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The Moon's plane of orbit slowly moves across the map display because the Earth is rotating under it. As soon as it approaches your current location, you will take off."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:20
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Because the northern latitude of your location is slightly higher than the inclination of the Moon's orbit, the optimal launch time is the instant when the northernmost point of the Moon's orbit plane is just south of Florida (launching due east)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:21
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "For launch sites closer to the equator, it is best to launch when the Moon's orbit plane crosses the site. Launch heading is then North-east or South-east, to match the orbital plane."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:23
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to launch window..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:26
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Earth is rotating east with respect to the Moon's orbital plane and the two orbit lines are moving towards alignment in the map display. The 'RInc' indicator in the left MFD display is counting down ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:28
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The Moon's orbital plane has now reached its optimum alignment with your position, and the relative inclination is at minimum (the 'Rate' readout in the left MFD display shows zero). Now is the time to launch."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:30
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Ready for takeoff - main engines powering up to maximum thrust."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:32
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Rotate."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:33
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Gear up."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:35
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Turning east for ascent to orbit, matching the Moon's orbit inclination."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:37
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The plane alignment MFD provides a rough guide for the correct ascent heading. Try to keep the relative inclination between your and the Moon's orbit at a minimum (indicated by the 'RInc' readout)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:38
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Initial climb rate is 30° to leave the denser part of the atmosphere quickly. You can use the trim control to adjust the pitch angle."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:39
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "By a happy coincidence, you get a glimpse of your final destination - the Moon - directly ahead in the centre of the screen."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:42
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "During ascent, the pitch angle can be adjusted with trim or manual elevator controls. From the initial 30°, it should slowly turn towards the horizontal."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:43
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We are aiming to reach orbital velocity and a horizontal flight path vector at an initial altitude of about 60km."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:44
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "As you leave the denser parts of the atmosphere behind, the spaceplane no longer generates enough lift to maintain the initial pitch angle. The flight path marker (the circle with a cross) will start to move down, indicating that the ascent slope is decreasing."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:46
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Now is a good time to switch to Orbit MFD mode to see how the orbital ascent is progressing."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:47
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "On the right MFD, click 'SEL', 'Orbit'. Then click 'PRJ' to select your current orbit as the projection plane, and 'DST' to switch to altitude readout mode."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:48
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You have reached orbit when the green ellipse (representing your orbital trajectory) rises above the grey circle (representing the surface of the Earth), and the periapsis altitude readout (PeA, the lowest point of the orbit) is positive and sufficiently high above the denser part of the atmosphere."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:50
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to orbit insertion ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:53
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "(By the way, the bright object left of centre on your screen is Saturn. You can display labels for celestial objects by pressing F9)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:56
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Main engine cut-off (MECO)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:57
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Because we have left the denser layers of the atmosphere behind us, attitude control is switched from the now ineffective aerodynamic control surfaces to the reaction control system."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:59
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The current orbit has a very low perigee altitude (PeA). To stabilise it, we will have to perform a circularisation burn at the next apogee passage."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:61
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The first manoever will however be a plane alignment with the Moon's orbital plane. This will be performed at the next node passage."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:63
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You should now switch the HUD display from 'Surface' to 'Orbit' mode. Orbit mode is more useful for orbital and interplanetary operations. It displays a pitch ladder and direction tape relative to the orbital plane, while the Surface HUD indicators are relative to the local horizon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:64
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The easiest way to select the Orbit HUD is by clicking the 'HUD' button on the Orbit MFD. Using this method also copies the orbit reference body (Earth in this case) to the HUD."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:66
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to node passage ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:69
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You are now approaching the intersection (node) with the Moon's orbital plane ('DN' marker in the Align Plane MFD display)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:70
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is the point where the plane alignment maneuver takes place to match your orbital plane with that of the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:71
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This burn adds a velocity difference ('Delta-V') perpendicular to your orbital plane, so we need to rotate the spacecraft."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:72
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Activating the 'Normal+' attitude program."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:73
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Remember - for a plane alignment burn (with main engines), turn 'NML+' at descending note (DN), and 'NML-' at ascending node (AN)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:74 Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:88
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Main engines engaged."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:75
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note how the RInc readout is counting down."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:76 Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:123
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Main engine cut-off."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:77
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The relative inclination ('RInc') with the Moon's orbital plane is now down to 0.02°. That's good enough!"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:78
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "In preparation for the next maneuver, we are turning into the flight path (by activating the 'Prograde' attitude mode)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:79
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to orbit circularisation burn ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:83
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You are now approaching apogee - the highest point of the orbit."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:84
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is location for the orbit circularisation burn, required to raise the perigee (lowest point of the orbit) for a stable orbit configuration."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:86
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This will be a short prograde burn, adding a velocity component in the direction of the flight path."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:87
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Re-aligning attitude with flight path vector."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:89
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Main engine cut-off (this was a low Delta-V burn)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:91
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The perigee altitude has now increased to about 250km, and the orbit eccentricty value of 0.0007 indicates a nearly circular orbit."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:93
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You now have to prepare for the next maneuver - the insertion into the trans-lunar orbit (TLI), which will bring you all the way to the moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:94
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Bring up the Transfer MFD mode on the left display: Press 'SEL' and 'Transfer'."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:95
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "First, you need to select the target body. Press 'TGT', <Enter>, type 'moon', <Enter>."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:96
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "To plan your transfer orbit, press 'HTO' (hypothetical transfer orbit)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:97
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Next, you need to add a Delta-V impulse at your orbit ejection point. Press, and hold down, 'DV+', until the 'Dv' readout shows 3.121k (meaning 3.121km/s). If you overshoot, press 'DV-' to reduce the ejection velocity."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:98
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Your planned transfer orbit should now be displayed as a dashed green ellipse. The leading intersection with the Moon's orbit (the yellow circle) is shown as a grey line."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:99
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The predicted position of the Moon at the time when you cross the Moon's orbit, is shown as a dashed yellow line."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:100
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You now have to try and match the grey and the dashed yellow lines, so that both you and the Moon reach the intersection point simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:101
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is done by adjusting the time of the ejection burn, using the 'EJ-' and 'EJ+' buttons."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:102
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Press 'EJ-' and 'EJ+' until the lines match. The 'TLe' readout should read approximately 11°."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:103
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The dashed green line now indicates the position of the orbit ejection burn. As soon as your current position (solid green line) matches it, the ejection burn will be performed."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:104
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to ejection burn ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:106
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Sunrise over Australia ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:108
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Main engines engaged for orbit ejection burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:109
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The Dv readout is counting down as the actual orbit velocity approaches that of the planned transfer orbit."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:110
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "As soon as Dv reaches zero, translunar orbit insertion will be complete, and the engines will be cut."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:119
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is a long burn, so I am fast-forwarding to the end ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:122
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Towards the end of the burn the orbit (solid green ellipse) starts growing rapidly, so you may want to reduce thrust to avoid overshooting."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:124
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Your orbit should now match the planned transfer orbit in the Transfer MFD display."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:125
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You can press 'HTO' again to turn off the hypothetical orbit. This will update the data readouts to refer to your actual orbit."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:126
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We are now en-route to the moon. This will be a long (and hopefully uneventful) coasting phase, so I am fast-forwarding to the mid-course correction maneuver."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:127
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast forwarding ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:133
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Dropping out of time warp for a mid-course correction."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:135
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We have now left the sphere of influence (SOI) of Earth's gravitational field (check the 'G' value at the bottom of the Orbit MFD indicating the fractional contribution of Earth to the present gravitational field)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:136
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Therefore you should now switch to the Moon as orbit reference for your instruments. On the Orbit MFD, click 'AR' (auto reference) to select the strongest gravitational source, which is now the Moon. Then click 'HUD' to copy the new reference to the HUD."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:138
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Because we want to land directly at Brighton Beach base, we need to rotate the plane of our lunar orbit so that it passes over the base. This plane change requires less Delta-V (and thus less fuel) while we are still far from the moon, so let's do it now."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:139
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Switch the left MFD to Map mode: Click 'SEL', 'Map', click 'REF', and select 'Earth' > 'Moon'."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:140
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The white square on the map is Brighton Beach. To mark it as a target, click 'TGT', and select 'Spaceports'->'Brighton Beach'. This will show the base location, distance and bearing at the bottom of the display."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:141
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The green line is the projection of the current orbital plane onto the moon's surface. We want to rotate the plane so that it crosses over the target base."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:142
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "To line up the glider for the alignment burn, we activate the 'Normal+' navigation mode."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:143
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "(Why NML+? We are orbiting the Moon retrograde. The flight path vector points west. This also means that the NML+ direction points south. By adding Delta-V in this direction, we will bend the western part of the orbit south, the eastern part north.)"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:144
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging 'Normal+' attitude mode to prepare for a plane-change burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:145
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "As the main engines fire, the orbit bends out of the moon's equatorial plane, until it intersects the target base."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:146
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Done. Note that the the alignment will not remain perfect, because the Moon (and the base with it) slowly rotates below our orbit. But this can easily be fixed later with a correction burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:148
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "With the orbital plane aligned, the next step is to adjust the periapsis (or in this case, the perilune) distance, that is, the point of closest approach to the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:149
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Currently, the orbit is intersecting the Moon's surface, so we need to raise the periapsis altitude (PeA) above zero."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:150
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This is an in-plane burn. Since we are not at periapsis, I am using a wild guess for a reasonable burn direction - 50° off the flight path."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:151
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging main engines."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:152
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engines cut-off. Perilune altitude is now approximately 150km."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:153
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Note that the orbit parameter readouts are not very reliable yet, because of strong field perturbations from the Sun and Earth. You will notice that the PeA readout is decreasing as we approach the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:154
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This completes the midcourse correction. Turning prograde for a good view as we approach the Moon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:155
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast forwarding to perilune ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:159
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The next maneuver is the lunar orbit insertion. This will be a retrograde burn at perilune, to close the orbit and lower the apoapsis distance."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:160 Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:182
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Turning retrograde."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:161
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging main engines for lunar orbit insertion."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:162
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engine cut-off. The orbit is now approximately circular, with an altitude of 120km."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:163
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The base is on the opposite side of the Moon. I am turning prograde again while we prepare for the last part of the trip."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:164
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Fast-forwarding to base approach ..."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:166
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Passing the terminator into the lunar day."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:174
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Dropping out of warp for the final part of the journey."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:175
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You are now about 1000km from your landing site. Time for a few preparations."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:176
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Click 'ZM+' on the Map MFD to increase the magnification, keeping both your location and the base in view. Keep zooming as you approach the base, to monitor your approach path."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:178
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Set the right MFD display to VTOL (vertical takeoff and landing) mode: Press 'SEL', 'VOR/VTOL'."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:179
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The NAV receiver frequency should be pre-set to 116.3MHz (The frequency of the radio beacon at Brighton Beach). We are still too far away to receive a signal, but will soon get into range."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:181
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "To land at the base, you need to drop out of orbit soon. This will require a retrograde burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:185
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Press 'H' to set the HUD to surface mode."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:186
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging 'Horizon level' mode to align attitude with the local horizon."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:187
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging main thrusters for orbit departure."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:188
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "When timing the deorbit burn, be careful not to be late (to avoid overshooting). If you deorbit too early, you will waste fuel on hovering above the surface."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:189
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "To estimate the minimum safe distance from base for the deorbit burn with main engines, try a little mental arithmetic:"
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:190
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "With the current fuel load, the main engines can produce an acceleration of about a = 20m/s². Orbital speed is about 1600m/s."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:191
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "This means that it will take t = v/a = 80s to kill the ground speed at full main thrust. In that time we will cover a distance of x = vt - ½at² = 64km. We must start the deceleration burn before getting closer than that to the base (or correspondingly earlier if you want to use the less powerful retros for braking)."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:193
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "By now you are within range of the Brighton Beach NAV beacon. The circular display in the VTOL MFD represents a top-down view with your position in the centre, and forward direction at 12 o'clock."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:194
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The direction of the base is indicated by the green line (it's behind you). Your velocity vector is the yellow arrow."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:195
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The flight path is not perfectly aligned, so we perform an adjustment burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:196
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "We turn the craft so that applying main thrust will push the flight path vector towards the base direction."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:197
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Engaging main engines for flight path correction."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:198
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Done, rotating back to retrograde."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:200
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "The horizontal situation is covered with the VTOL display, so you can switch the left MFD to Surface mode: Click 'SEL', 'Surface'."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:201
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Distance to base 300km, altitude 100km. Performing another deceleration burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:203
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Opening the retro engine covers to prepare for retro deceleration burns."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:210
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Distance to base 100km, altitude 56km. Another deceleration burn."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:212
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Adding hover thrust to reduce sink rate."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:214
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Finally we are turning towards the base for final approach."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:218
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "In the last phase of the base approach, you need to balance your horizontal and vertical velocity components. The flight path marker helps with this. Keep it above the base for correct approach slope."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:219
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "If it drops too low, increase hover thrust."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:226
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "On the VTOL MFD, click 'NAV' to switch to Nav receiver 2. This is preset to the pad 1 transmitter frequency, your designated landing pad."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:230
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Distance 1.2km from base, altitude 10km."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:231
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Use the RCS in linear mode to fine-tune your position above the pad."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:235
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Gear down."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:238
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Altitude 1000m, horizontal displacement from pad 40m."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:239
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Use the hover thrusters to adjust your vertical speed for a soft touch down."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:241
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "You are now exactly centered above the pad."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:243
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "400m above the surface."
msgstr ""

#: Flights/DG to the moon/system.dat:245
